# /etc/fw_env.config — libubootenv (fw_setenv/fw_printenv) on Amlogic A113D
#
# Amlogic AML registers /dev/nand_env as a single 64KB chardev (NOT an mtd
# partition) backed by the AML NFL driver. There is no second redundant
# copy and no flash erase block size for libubootenv to honor.
#
# Format: <device> <offset> <env_size>
# Single-instance env => only one line.
#
# Live-validated on .78 (S19k Pro am3-aml) on 2026-04-29:
# /dev/nand_env is standard U-Boot env format (little-endian CRC32 over
# bytes 4..end, followed by null-terminated key=value entries). There is no
# redundant env copy.
#
# S99upgrade still treats the recovery-flag byte at mtd5+0x05300000 as the
# load-bearing boot commit, and uses fw_setenv firstboot=0 as the matching
# U-Boot env commit.

/dev/nand_env  0x0000  0x10000
